{"questionId":"13117","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The voltage <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span> in a circuit is given by the equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\\left( t \\right) = 3\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {100\\pi t} \\right)\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t \\geqslant 0\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>⩾</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> is measured in seconds.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The current <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"i\">\n  <mi>i</mi>\n</math></span> in this circuit is given by the equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"i\\left( t \\right) = 2\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {100\\pi \\left( {t + 0.003} \\right)} \\right)\">\n  <mi>i</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>0.003</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The power <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span> in this circuit is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( t \\right) = v\\left( t \\right) \\times i\\left( t \\right)\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mi>i</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The average power&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{p_{av}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> in this circuit from <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 0\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> to <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = T\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>T</mi>\n</math></span> is given by the equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{p_{av}}\\left( T \\right) = \\frac{1}{T}\\int_0^T {p\\left( t \\right){\\text{d}}t} \">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>p</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>(</mo>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mo>)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>d</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T > 0\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{p_{av}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>(0.007).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{p_{av}} = \\frac{1}{{0.007}}\\int_0^{0.007} {6\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {100\\pi t} \\right)} {\\text{sin}}\\left( {100\\pi \\left( {t + 0.003} \\right)} \\right){\\text{d}}t\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.007</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.007</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>sin</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>(</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>100</mn>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>0.003</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>=&nbsp;2.87 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13117","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ1.H_10e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find p a v (0.007).","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.12—Areas under a curve onto x or y axis. Volumes of revolution about x and y","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}